During this task, you will first encounter an 8x8 grid filled with black and gray cells. Press the left button for symmetric and press the right button for asymmetric.

When you make a response, a new 8x8 grid will appear, and you should complete as many correct symmetry judgments as you can. After each set of 8x8 grids, a 4x4 grid will have one cell colored black. You should remember the cellâ€™s location.

This sequence of 8x8 grids and 4x4 grid will alternate four times. After the fourth time, a blank 4x4 grid will be presented.

On the blank 4x4 grid, use the buttons to navigate the grid and the center button to select the cells you think were colored black in the preceding 4 4x4 grids. Select them in the order they were shown.

It's important to respond promptly when the grid appears, as the screen will move on automatically after a limited time.
